******
[2] Cholera - South Sudan (Upper Nile)
Date: Fri 18 Jul 2014
Source: Radio Tamazuj [edited]
https://radiotamazuj.org/en/article/cholera-kills-five-more-people-fashoda-county


Health workers in Fashoda County in South Sudan's Upper Nile State said there have been about 18 cases of cholera with 5 deaths in the last 2 weeks [about 4-18 Jul 2014]. The infected citizens are currently getting medical attention at cholera treatment centers established by Doctors Without Borders [MSF] and South Sudan Society of Red Cross [SSRCS] at Lol and Poul villages.

Dr. Olau Alou, the Fashoda County Medical Services Director, told Radio Tamazuj on Wednesday [16 Jul 2014] that the 5 fatalities and the 18 confirmed cholera cases were from Lol and Poul areas. The official also expressed concern about the spread of the outbreak to the neighboring areas in Upper Nile. He attributed the problem to the movements of infected people to areas where there are no health facilities, which makes it difficult to contain the outbreak.

Alou noted the 13 [remaining] patients are now receiving treatment at therapeutic centers, saying the county headquarters have not recorded any cholera cases so far. "The MSF and SSRCS [South Sudan Red Cross Society] have opened about 3 cholera treatment centers in Lol, Kodok and Poul areas," he explained.

Last week [week ending 13 Jul 2014], a medical assistant in Kodok Payam Hospital told Radio Tamazuj that 4 people died of cholera and about 100 cholera cases were recorded in the Lol area alone.

